Police have impounded close to one million litres of adulterated fuel in three godowns in industrial area, Nairobi.They also arrested more than 100 suspects, believed to be part of a cartel that deals in illicit fuel, during a raid on Friday.Nairobi CID chief Ireri Kamwende said at the scene that lorries from major oil companies are driven into the yard and loaded with adulterated fuel which is sold to unsuspecting petrol station operators.Kamwende said the unscrupulous dealers mix diesel with paraffin.Lorries belonging to two major companies were found in one of the three godowns; one was branded Kenol Kobil and another National Oil.They were among tens of vehicles found parked at the location.